<head>TOAST</head>
    <list type="altnames">
<item>DRINK (TO) THE HEALTH OF</item>
<item>DRINK TO</item>
<item>SALUTE</item>
<item>HONOR</item>
<item>PAY TRIBUTE TO</item>
    </list>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">祝酒</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>DRINK TOGETHER with OTHERS AND SAY that one CONGRATULATES someone OR CELEBRATES SOMETHING.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The host offering a first toast to his guest is xiàn 獻 (xiàn jiǔ 獻酒 ) "offer a toast to the guest".</p>
<p>2. The guest toasting back at a feast is zuò 醋 / 酢 "offer a toast back to the host".</p>
<p>3. The host responding to the guest's toast is chóu 酬 "toast back to the guest".</p>
        </div>
<div type="huang-jingui">
<p>HUANG JINGUI 2006</p>
<p>FOOD 5.</p>
<p>獻，主人向客人敬酒。</p>
<p>酢，客人敬謝主人之酒。</p>
<p>酬，主人再謝賓敬酒。</p>
        </div>
